test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7507aefd6a00>([76])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7507aefd6a00> = [[1, 76], [1, 76, 1], [76], [76, 1], [1, 76], [1, 76, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7507aefd6a00>([1, 76])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7507aefd6a00> = [[1, 76], [1, 76, 1], [76], [76, 1], [1, 76], [1, 76, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7507aefd6a00>([76, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7507aefd6a00> = [[1, 76], [1, 76, 1], [76], [76, 1], [1, 76], [1, 76, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 76
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
